Preamble
The LaTeX Project Public License (LPPL) is the standard license for software distributed by the LaTeX project. It is intended to ensure that the material is always available and that it can be used, copied, modified, and distributed.

A particular goal of this license is that the integrity of the Work is maintained. This means that if you distribute a modified version of the Work, you must clearly distinguish it from the original version. This protects the reputation of the original maintainer (pacure) and ensures that users do not encounter "broken" versions thinking they are the official ones.

1. Definitions
Work: The collection of files distributed by the Maintainer (pacure).

Base Required File: Any file that is part of the Work.

Compiled Work: The result of processing the Work (e.g., an executable or a trained model file).

Maintainer: pacure.

2. Conditions on Copying and Distribution
You may distribute a complete, unmodified copy of the Work. Distribution of only part of the Work is considered a modification.

3. Conditions on Modification and Distribution of Modified Versions
You may modify a copy of the Work and distribute that modified version, provided that you meet all of the following conditions:

a. You must ensure that the modified Work is clearly identified as a Derived Work, and not the original version.

b. You must not use the name of the original Maintainer (pacure) or any name that implies their endorsement, unless you have explicit permission.

c. If the Work contains a "Main Guide" or primary file, you must include a prominent notice stating that the file is a modified version and where the original can be found.

d. You must ensure that any modified file does not interfere with the stability of the original Work for other users.

4. Maintenance of the Work
The Work has the status "author-maintained". The Current Maintainer is pacure.

5. No Warranty
There is no warranty for the Work. Except when otherwise stated in writing, the copyright holder (pacure) provides the Work "as is" without warranty of any kind, either expressed or implied. The entire risk as to the quality and performance of the Work is with you.

6. Limitation of Liability
In no event will pacure be liable to you for damages, including any general, special, incidental, or consequential damages arising out of the use or inability to use the Work (including but not limited to loss of data or data being rendered inaccurate).
